videos.description: Notre Dame QB Brandon Wimbush starts off with a big 35-yard pass to Equanimeous St. Brown down the sideline.
videos.headline: Wimbush opens for Notre Dame with 35-yard pass

videos.description: Brandon Wimbush bursts through the line for a 31-yard run up the sideline for the Fighting Irish.
videos.headline: Wimbush breaks off 31-yard run

videos.description: LSU running back Derrius Guice throws his tackler to the ground with a stiff arm and scrambles for 31 yards.
videos.headline: Guice stiff arms his way for 31-yard run

videos.description: LSU punter Zach Von Rosenberg mishandles the long snap but recovers the ball and fires off a 47-yard punt.
videos.headline: LSU punter bobbles snap, recovers for big punt

videos.description: LSU quarterback Danny Etling is met by the LSU defense just outside the end zone keeping the game scoreless.
videos.headline: Notre Dame gets a big 3rd-down stop at the goal line

videos.description: Fighting Irish backup quarterback Ian Book takes off for a 21-yard gain diving for a first down.
videos.headline: Notre Dame's Book scrambles to keep drive alive

videos.description: LSU head coach Ed Orgeron has complete confidence that his team's offense will get going in the second half against Notre Dame.
videos.headline: Orgeron: 'We'll get the running game going in the 2nd'

videos.description: LSU catches some luck as their punt ricochets off the leg of a Notre Dame player and is recovered by Blake Ferguson for the Tigers.
videos.headline: LSU recovers muffed punt

videos.description: Danny Etling dumps a short pass to Derrius Guice, who races for the end zone and leaps in for a 20-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Guice dives in for LSU's first TD

videos.description: Fighting Irish special teams lose sight of the ball on a short kick off but catch some luck with the recovery.
videos.headline: Notre Dame loses track of ball on kickoff

videos.description: Notre Dame quarterback Ian Book throws an errant pass that is picked off by Greedy Williams along the sideline.
videos.headline: Book picked off by LSU in red zone

videos.description: Tigers quarterback Danny Etling finds Foster Moreau with a pin-point pass for a 26-yard gain.
videos.headline: Etling fires sideline pass to Moreau for LSU

videos.description: Danny Etling rolls out and hits Derrius Guice with a short two-yard pass for an easy Tiger touchdown.
videos.headline: Etling connects with Guice for LSU's 2nd TD

videos.description: Irish running back Dexter Williams gets away from a few LSU defenders on his way to a 31-yard run.
videos.headline: ND's Williams slips multiple tackles on 31-yard run

videos.description: ND's Ian Book finds Michael Young for a six-yard tocuhdown pass and then flips the ball to Josh Adams who pushes in for the two-point conversion to tie it at 14.
videos.headline: Notre Dame ties it with 2-pt conversion in 4th quarter

videos.description: LSU's Derrius Guice is stopped inches from the goal line on 3rd down as his team settles for a field goal to take a 17-14 lead.
videos.headline: Guice comes up short of the end zone

videos.description: Miles Boykin makes an incredible fingertip catch on the sideline and dodges defenders on his way to a 55-yard touchdown to give the Irish the lead.
videos.headline: Boykin reels in outrageous 1-handed TD catch

videos.description: Notre Dame QB Ian Book explains how much winning 10 games means during a 'rebuilding year' after a Citrus Bowl victory over LSU.
videos.headline: ND's Book: '10 wins means so much'

videos.description: Notre Dame head coach Brian Kelly says his team battled through a difficult schedule and made their fans proud with a Citrus Bowl victory.
videos.headline: Kelly: 'This season was transformational'

videos.description: The Fighting Irish score a late touchdown to beat LSU 21-17 in the Citrus Bowl.
